          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-11 12:14:03" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a portable dwelling of cloth and/or skins, held up by poles and fastened by cords to stakes</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>tent</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages ‘tent’ is simply ‘a house made of cloth.’ One should avoid terms which would imply a military tent or a temporary shelter used only on vacations or holidays. In OT times such tents were permanent dwellings of nomadic groups and were moved from place to place as livestock were transferred from one pasture area to another.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
